# SMART ATTENDANCE V2 - AI INSTRUCTIONS

## 1. PROJECT SCOPE & SCALE
- [cite_start]Scale: 100 branches, 5,000 employees[cite: 4, 12].
- [cite_start]Main goal: Smart check-in via WiFi (SSID/BSSID) and GPS Geofencing[cite: 5, 6].
- [cite_start]Priority: Anti-fraud (No Fake GPS, No VPN)[cite: 6].

## 2. TECH STACK
- Frontend & Backend: Next.js 14 (App Router).
- UI: Tailwind CSS + Shadcn UI + Lucide Icons.
- Database: PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM.
- [cite_start]Deployment: Docker & Docker Compose.

## 3. DATABASE STRATEGY
- [cite_start]Multi-branch support: All tables must relate to a Branch ID[cite: 12].
- [cite_start]Performance: Use proper indexing for 5,000 users and daily check-in logs[cite: 12].
- [cite_start]API: Implement pagination and filtering for all list views[cite: 12].

## 4. DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW
- [cite_start]Git Flow: main (stable), develop (staging), feature/* (tasks)[cite: 15].
- Commits: Use Conventional Commits (feat, fix, chore)[cite: 16].
- AI Workflow: Spec -> Generate -> Review -> Test -> Commit[cite: 20].

## 5. ANTI-FRAUD LOGIC (CREATIVE)
- Verify both WiFi BSSID and GPS coordinates.
- Requirement: If GPS is suspicious, fallback to FaceID/Biometric (WebAuthn).